1. Sign up for alchemy: https://alchemy.com/signup/eth
   -	Alchemy is a blockchain developer platform that allows us to communicate with the Ethereum chain.


2. Install metamask extension: https://metamask.io/download.html
   - A virtual wallet which will give us an Ethereum account to send and receive transactions 
   - Make sure to use Ropsten Test Network for any test development

3. Send Ropsten Test Etherum to your Metamask wallet from a faucet:
  https://fauceth.komputing.org/
  -	A faucet is an application that distributes small amounts of cryptocurrencies

4. Check your balance using Alchemyâ€™s composer tool: https://composer.alchemyapi.io/?composer_state=%7B%22network%22%3A0%2C%22methodName%22%3A%22eth_getBalance%22%2C%22paramValues%22%3A%5B%22%22%2C%22latest%22%5D%7D

6. update .env with your public key, private key, and alchemy application url

5. run npm i

6. We are using HardHat development environment
   https://hardhat.org/getting-started/#overview

7. We are using  Open Zeppelin libraries: https://docs.openzeppelin.com/contracts/3.x/
- A library for smart contract development

8. Learn about ERC-721 standard:
   https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-721

9. npx hardhat compile
   npx hardhat --network ropsten run scripts/deploy.js

10. Use Ropsten Etherscan to see your contract deployed!
https://ropsten.etherscan.io/

11. Learn about ABIs:
https://docs.alchemy.com/alchemy/guides/eth_getlogs#what-are-ab-is
-	Application Binary Interface (ABI) is the interface that specifies how to interact with a specific Ethereum contract

12. Use Pinata to upload your image (or any other file): https://app.pinata.cloud

13.  update nft-metadata.json to include any information about your file

14. Upload your nft-metadata.json to Pinata also

15. update mint-nft.js mint function with the url to your nft-metadata.json file hash from Pinata
  e.g.:
  mintNFT(
    "ipfs://QmcQYw5Mc8xrSXucWPHw5gQ7JGCs798zTx73KegAcYCB2e"
  )

16. node scripts/mint-nft.js

17. check mempool cache https://dashboard.alchemyapi.io/mempool
